# Sabia Group HRBP Recovery Practice Dataset

## About the Project

This synthetic practice dataset was created by **Musa** as part of an HRBP and data analytics portfolio project.

The project simulates a business recovery case for **Sabia Group**, a fictional smartwatch manufacturing company in Bangladesh. It demonstrates how HR Business Partnering, workforce planning, people analytics, production data, and financial analysis can be connected to support business improvement.

> **Project philosophy:** We do not build systems only for the sake of building systems; we use systems to improve business performance.

## Business Scenario

Sabia Group entered smartwatch production without completing sufficient MVP and prototype validation. As a result, the business experienced:

- high product defect rates;
- low first-pass yield;
- excessive overtime;
- employee skill gaps;
- duplicated or mismatched roles;
- fragmented HR and production data;
- operational and financial losses.

The dataset supports a simulated Q1–Q4 recovery programme led by a strategic HRBP.

## What This Dataset Covers

The dataset includes practice data related to:

